divs: Sighting DetailsFour of us were traveling (by boat) south on the north end of Long Lake in northern Wisconsin. We saw a ball of light just above the horizon it was traveling east. The ball then split into five balls the four trailing balls were slightly smaller then the lead ball. All were evenly spaced. Within a minute they just vanished.
Summary: Ball of light splits in to five balls then disappears
